        <p>The email is well-received, but only partially solves the problem. Much like the <a class="anchor-body" href="/case-studies/groups-al" target="_blank">Action List</a>, it leaves much to be desired. Counselors and doctors appreciate this snapshot of their member cohort, but it is only a small piece of the puzzle. There is still so much they want to know, such as a more in-depth attendance and drug screen history, coupled with relevant insights and recommendations. They would also like to see the Panel Summary for other staff members, to help cover for them when they are out of office. This email is only the first step towards creating a fuller picture of a member's recovery journey for all staff members to access.</p>

        <p>After about 6 months, I was asked to reimagine the Panel Summary as part of our Digital Platform, instead of in an email. The Digital Platform is our custom patient portal that talks directly to our EHR platform (eClinicalWorks). It was created as part of our thoughtbot contract work <a class="anchor-body" href="/case-studies/groups" target="_blank">back in 2020</a>.  It was developed and designed by our team to serve as a more intuitive interface for staff to access the appointment data and medical records that live in our (clunky, difficult to navigate) EHR platform. Taking the Panel Summary out of a static email and into our Digital Platform meant it would become interactive and dynamic, and there would now be a sense of transparency and accountability among staff.</p>

