        <h3 class="article__heading">03. Outcome</h3>
        <p>I showed these designs in another round of staff user interviews and overall the feedback was very positive. They are delighted by its simple design and thoughtful organization. They appreciate the mix of visual elements with text, for it makes the information more digestible and easy to read. The bar charts give them a clear overview of the past three months, while the warnings and badges help them identify and prioritize which actions to take. Overall, they are so happy about having all of the member's information presented in one place. This will minimize the time spent cross-referencing other sources and digging for information ‚Äì which will allow them to focus on the member and their needs.</p>

        <p>The next steps are to pilot it among a small subset of staff, so we can learn and refine before we release to the larger group. My team and I are all excited to measure its impact on the organization and the member experience at Groups, which we believe will be very positive. By creating the Panel Summary, we are providing staff with the tools, insights, and confidence needed to give members with the best care possible ‚Äì which is a huge win for everyone!</p>

